[normal]How will the policies set out in the Government’s “Action for Roads” command paper improve the strategic road network for all road users, whilst also impr
[normal]oving the environment?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How does the Government’s policy for roads link with planning for other transport modes?
[normal]How reliable is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the strategic road network? How should the Government deal with unc
[normal]ertainty in its forecast?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on the strategic road network? What impact will new technology have?
[normal]What mechanisms are
[normal] there for Government to increase investment in strategic roads and attract new investors? Are there good examples from other countries that could be applied in the UK? 
[normal]How should the 
[normal]Highways Agency be reformed to make it “the world’s leading highway operator”? What roles should Government and the private sector play to ensure better management of the strategic road network?
